==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Besiege
<hw>Be*siege"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Besieged</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Besieging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bisegen</ets>; pref. <ets>be-</ets> + <ets>segen</ets> to siege.
See <er>Siege</er>.]</ety> <def>To beset or surround with armed forces,
for the purpose of compelling to surrender; to lay siege to; to
beleaguer; to beset.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Till Paris was <qex>besieged</qex>, famished, and lost.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To environ; hem in; invest; encompass.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besiegement</ent>⟦br⟧
